<LegalLayout
  title="Cookies Policy"
  description="How emergedigital.com uses cookies and similar technologies, and how you can control them."
>
  <p>
    This policy explains how Emerge Digital IT Solutions LLC (<strong>"Emerge Digital"</strong>)
    uses cookies and similar technologies on <strong>emergedigital.com</strong>. It should be read
    alongside our <a href="/legal/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>What cookies are</h2>
  <p>
    Cookies are small text files placed on your device when you visit a website. They let the site
    function correctly and help us understand how the site is used so we can improve it.
  </p>

  <h2>The cookies we use</h2>
  <p><strong>Strictly necessary.</strong> These are required for the site to operate — for example to handle page navigation and to keep the site secure. They cannot be switched off in our systems.</p>
  <p><strong>Analytics.</strong> We use Google Analytics 4 to collect aggregated, mostly anonymous information about how visitors use the site — which pages are popular, how people arrive, and how the site performs. This helps us improve content and usability.</p>
  <p>We do <strong>not</strong> use advertising, retargeting, or third-party marketing cookies on this site.</p>

  <h2>Managing cookies</h2>
  <p>
    You can control and delete cookies through your browser settings, and you can block analytics
    cookies at any time. Most browsers let you refuse or remove cookies; doing so may affect some
    site functionality. You can also opt out of Google Analytics using Google's
    <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" rel="noopener">browser add-on</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this policy as our use of cookies changes. The date at the top of this page shows when it was last revised.</p>

  <h2>Contact us</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about our use of cookies? Email
    <a href="mailto:rami@emergedigital.com">rami@emergedigital.com</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
